{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "New legislation to regulate how online marketplaces manage seller accounts",
        "additional_details": "Sellers may be asked to provide documents that are impossible to produce, while platforms may to deduct fees from suspended accounts. \r\n \r\nWe think this has caused serious financial harm, including loss of income, business closure, and even eviction for some. In many cases, suspended sellers may lose access to their accounts and may be unable to respond to requests or communicate with customers. \r\n \r\nWe are calling for legislation requiring platforms to: provide clear suspension reasons, offer a fair appeals process, stop charging fees during suspension, and release funds unless fraud is proven.",
        "background": "Many small businesses rely on online marketplaces such as Amazon but may face account suspensions and withheld earnings without clear reasons or due process. ",
